---
import SectionHeading from "~/components/ui/SectionHeading.astro";
import Tag from "~/components/ui/Tag.astro";

/* DRAFT — every paragraph below is written by Claude. Rewrite in your voice. */
/* Core competencies — synced with resume PDF. 11 chips, technical domains
   first then leadership/program signals. */
const competencies = [
  "Power Electronics",
  "Sonar & Acoustics",
  "Undersea Systems & Autonomy",
  "Directed Energy / HEL",
  "Systems Engineering",
  "Hardware Lifecycle",
  "R&D Leadership",
  "Technical Leadership",
  "System Architecture",
  "Team Management",
  "Program Execution",
];
---

<section id="about" aria-labelledby="about-heading" class="scroll-mt-24">
  <SectionHeading title="About" />

  <div class="space-y-5 text-slate">
    {/* DRAFT */}
    <p>
      I'm a senior electrical and systems engineering leader with two decades
      of experience taking complex hardware from a sketch on a whiteboard to a
      delivered, integrated system. Today I lead the power electronics and
      system design group at General Atomics Electromagnetic Systems in San
      Diego, where my team supports high-energy laser and electro-optical
      programs for the U.S. Department of Defense.
    </p>

    {/* DRAFT */}
    <p>
      My career has moved between three closely related worlds: directed
      energy with the Layered Laser Defense prototype at Lockheed Martin and
      the Reaper-mounted high-energy laser at GA-EMS, undersea autonomy with
      the Marlin AUV, Terradepth's long-endurance vehicles, and the RAP-VLA
      passive surveillance system, and Navy sonar with MK54, LWWAA, HELRAS,
      TB-29, and TB-34A as Chief Engineer at L3Harris. I hold a Master's in
      Electrical Engineering from Johns Hopkins focused on power electronics
      and analog circuit design, and an active Top Secret clearance.
    </p>

    {/* DRAFT */}
    <p>
      Outside of my day job I'm open to advisory work for small businesses,
      startups, and prime contractors who need a senior pair of eyes — design
      reviews, architecture critiques, technical due diligence, or hands-on
      help framing a difficult hardware problem. If you're building anything
      that involves power conversion, batteries in punishing environments,
      directed-energy subsystems, or unmanned maritime platforms, I'd like to
      hear about it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-2" aria-label="Core competencies">
    {competencies.map((c) => <li><Tag label={c} /></li>)}
  </ul>
</section>
